The funny part was bringing them to the bar(different bar that doesn’t serve food) and left it on the table. People from my pool team would come over and steal a fry, every single one of them took a bite and threw it out. I may try one more time but so far not impressed at all and quite frankly 10 bucks for a wrap with fries that is super small, doesn’t make me wanna go back but hey maybe the cook was having a bad day

Excellent food in a classic bar.. The food is chef- quality. My wife and I had appetizer plates, and they were great. Who expects to find lollipop lamb chops as an app? They were on a bed of wilted spinach that was spectacular. We also had tenderloin tips that came with sauteed button mushrooms.. wonderful! Wednesday night is wing night, too. Lastly, a siracha mayo topped mushroom stuffed with crab stuffing was all that you hoped for. David, our server, was superb. The live music was great, too. The only downside is indoor smoking, but there is an outside area  to eat in.
